    • Method Detail

      • pipe

        public static void pipe​(InputStream in,
                        OutputStream out,
                        int bufsize)
                 throws IOException
        Reads all bytes from the specified input stream and writes them to the specified output stream. Bytes are read and written in chunks of bufsize length. Both the input stream and the output stream are first wrapped into a BufferedInputStream c.q. BufferedOutputStream if they aren't already instances of those classes. Neither the input stream nor the output stream is closed when done.
        Parameters:
        in - The input stream
        out - The output stream
        bufsize - The buffer size
        Throws:
        IOException - If an I/O error occurs

      • createTempFile

        public static File createTempFile​(Class<?> requester,
                                  String extension)
                           throws IOException
        Creates a File object for a new, empty file in the file system's temp directory. Using File.createTempFile(String, String) may fail if temporary files are created in rapid succession as it seems to use only System.currentTimeMillis() to invent a file name. This method has a 100% chance of generating a unique path.
        Parameters:
        requester - The class requesting the temp file (simple name will become part of the file name)
        extension - The extension to append to the generated file name
        Returns:
        A File object for a new, empty file in the file system's temp directory
        Throws:
        IOException - If an I/O error occurs
